article.description: Ge'Lawn Guyn made four 3-pointers and had 26 points to lead five scorers in double figures, and East Tennessee State defeated Wisconsin-Green Bay 103-90 on Tuesday.
article.headline: Guyn's 26 lead E. Tennessee St. in 103-90 win over Green Bay
article.linkText: Guyn's 26 lead E. Tennessee St. in 103-90 win over Green Bay
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. -- Ge'Lawn Guyn made four 3-pointers and had 26 points to lead five scorers in double figures, and East Tennessee State defeated Wisconsin-Green Bay 103-90 on Tuesday. The Buccaneers (2-0) got 17 points from T.J. Cromer, 12 from Isaac Banks and 10 apiece from A.J. Merriweather and Abednego Lufile. Kenneth Lowe scored 23 points to lead the Phoenix (0-2). Carrington Love had 22 points, Jordan Fouse added 15 points and 13 rebounds and Charles Cooper had 10 points. Lowe's basket pulled Green Bay to 71-67 midway through the second half. Lester Wilson's 3-pointer started a 23-13 East Tennessee State spurt that made it a 14-point game with 2 minutes left. Guyn also had eight rebounds, four assists, a steal and two blocked shots for East Tennessee State. The Buccaneers finished with nine blocks.
